  "text": "span the entire molecule, and the frequency of reactivity to the different epitopes varies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Remarkably, occasional high responses to certain peptides are also seen in controls (SI > 4), with no other sign of autoimmunity [CITATION_6] . In a pioneering study on in situ reactivity of persons at onset of type 1 diabetes and patients with long-standing disease, it has been shown that CTLs in HLA-A2 + individuals showed reactivity to single epitopes from 6 different autoantigens (preproinsulin included, epitope 15-23). There was an inversely proportional staining of pancreases with HLA-A2 tetramers with respect to age from diagnosis. In fact, no such reactivity was detected in any patients with over 10 years time from the date of onset of type 1 diabetes [CITATION_7] .",
